## üß™ Theoretical Basis

**NKTg Law of Variable Inertia**:  
An object's motion tendency in space depends on position `x`, velocity `v`, and mass `m`.

NKTg = f(x, v, m)

yaml
Copy
Edit

Where:
- `x`: position from a reference point
- `v`: velocity
- `m`: mass

Two pairwise interaction quantities:

- `NKTg‚ÇÅ = x √ó p`  
- `NKTg‚ÇÇ = (dm/dt) √ó p`  
With `p = m √ó v` (linear momentum)

Interpretation:
- If `NKTg‚ÇÅ > 0`: object tends to move away from stable state  
- If `NKTg‚ÇÅ < 0`: object returns to stable state  
- If `NKTg‚ÇÇ > 0`: mass variation supports motion  
- If `NKTg‚ÇÇ < 0`: mass variation resists motion  

